dismissalText.commentary: Rameez Shahzad c Cremer b Chatara 59 (61b 4x4 2x6 72m) SR: 96.72

dismissalComment.html: The Harare crowd finds its voice again. Rameez Shah backs away a fair way outside leg and aims to go inside-out over mid-off. He can't deal with the extra bounce and ends up splicing it squarer to extra cover. Captain Cremer settles under this skier. Redemption for Chatara after an inconsistent first spell

dismissalText.commentary: Peter Moor c Adnan Mufti b Qadeer Ahmed 39 (61b 2x4 0x6 108m) SR: 63.93

dismissalComment.html: Moor falls! And that's a soft dismissal at cover. Overpitched on off stump, and he tries to bunt it over the infield. Manages to take the bat's toe end, and sits up as an easy catch for the fielder. Silence once again at the HSC

Naveed beats Mire for pace and rushes a hook. The resultant top edge is well held by square leg. 137ks short ball, fizzes through outside off, Mire has to fetch it from outside off and is late onto his shot. Gone. What an early lift for UAE

Naveed hits 140ks and floors Hamilton's off stump. In-between length from Naveed again - neither driveable nor pullable - it keeps low to boot. Starts outside off and cuts back in to shoot through the defences of the opener. Zimbabwe lose their openers and the asking rate has nudged past 6

headshotImage.caption: Rameez Shahzad player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rameez Shahzad player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: full toss outside off, sliced over point and they only take a couple. UAE win! Zimbabwe lose by three runs, but they're not out yet. If tomorrow's game is tied, then they'd go through. But it doesn't look good for Zimbabwe right now: they're on the brink of elimination

commentPostTextItems.html: 6.13pm Another crazy encounter, another finish that went down to the wire. Zimbabwe are out - well, they could still qualify if tomorrow's game is a low-scoring tie, but the chances of that are way too low. Effectively tomorrow's game is a knockout for a spot in the 2019 World Cup. The winner goes through, the loser goes home. Zimbabwe will hope for a miraculous tie. Hope you enjoyed ESPNcricinfo's coverage of another nail-biter from the World Cup Qualifiers in Zimbabwe. Thanks for your company. Bye bye!

6.02 First up the winning captain Rohan Mustafa: "It's a big win for us, beating a Test team. No one knew about us, know they'll know about us. Feel sorry for Zimbabwe, but that's sport. Injuries hurt us in the Super sixes, but we have shown how much we've changed in the past 1.5 years. We'll come hard next time."
MSH: "Only hope for ZIM is for tomorrow's match to be a tie. "

Graeme Cremer: "(what went wrong?) We lost wickets in crucial periods. Taking nothing away from UAE, they bowled and fielded excellently. Credit to our team for holding our nerve in a few games through the tournament. We'll pick ourselves up soon, but right now it doesn't feel too good."
5.59pm Tomorrow's last super-six game, between Ireland and Afghanistan, will decide which of these two teams will qualify into the 2019 World Cup. Zimbabwe's dream is still alive, but barely.

Their NRR (0.42) has dropped below Ireland's (0.47), so even if tomorrow's game is washed out, Ireland will qualify. But in the case of a tie in tomorrow's game, Ireland's NRR will drop and Zimbabwe would go through. It's unlikely, but possible.
Word from the two captains in a moment.
Keyur: "How costly has that drop from raza proved to be"
Mohammad Naveed is the Man of the Match He says: "I bowled wicket to wicket and the yorker came off. Dedicate this to my brother."

5.54pm UAE have almost knocked Zimbabwe out of World Cup contention. They did well, trying to chase a rather inflated score of 230 in 40 overs, but it wasn't to be tonight. We could see a Zimbabwe-less World Cup for the first time since 1979!

commentPostTextItems.html: Oh man, another terrific super-six encounter. Can Zimbabwe make it to the 2019 World Cup?

milestones.description: Rohan Mustafa and Ghulam Shabber's 74-run partnership is UAE's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 70 between Indika Batuwitarachchi and Amjad Ali
Rameez Shahzad has broken the record for most sixes (17) in ODIs for UAE, going past Shaiman Anwar's 16
This is the lowest match aggregate (461) involving teams Zimbabwe & U.A.E. in ODIs
U.A.E.'s 9-run win against Zimbabwe is the smallest margin of victory in terms of runs in ODIs, beating 30-run win against Afghanistan
